{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":936,"text":"So I'm going to talk about work;"},{"time":2650,"text":"specifically, why people can't\nseem to get work done at work,"},{"time":6460,"text":"which is a problem we all kind of have."},{"time":8913,"text":"But let's sort of start at the beginning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11100,"text":"So, we have companies\nand non-profits and charities"},{"time":14730,"text":"and all these groups that have\nemployees or volunteers of some sort."},{"time":20198,"text":"And they expect these people\nwho work for them"},{"time":23928,"text":"to do great work --"},{"time":25634,"text":"I would hope, at least."},{"time":27000,"text":"At least good work, hopefully,\nat least it's good work --"},{"time":29739,"text":"hopefully great work."},{"time":31000,"text":"And so what they typically\ndo is they decide"},{"time":33072,"text":"that all these people need to come\ntogether in one place to do that work."},{"time":37000,"text":"So a company, or a charity,\nor an organization of any kind,"},{"time":39999,"text":"unless you're working in Africa,\nif you're really lucky to do that --"},{"time":44187,"text":"most people have to go\nto an office every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46444,"text":"And so these companies,"},{"time":48404,"text":"they build offices."},{"time":50153,"text":"They go out and they buy a building,\nor they rent a building,"},{"time":53073,"text":"or they lease some space,"},{"time":55000,"text":"and they fill this space with stuff."},{"time":58000,"text":"They fill it with tables, or desks,"},{"time":61000,"text":"chairs, computer equipment,"},{"time":63899,"text":"software, Internet access,"},{"time":67000,"text":"maybe a fridge, maybe a few other things,"},{"time":70269,"text":"and they expect their employees,\nor their volunteers,"},{"time":72874,"text":"to come to that location\nevery day to do great work."},{"time":75547,"text":"It seems like it's perfectly\nreasonable to ask that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78492,"text":"However, if you actually talk to people"},{"time":80849,"text":"and even question yourself,\nand you ask yourself,"},{"time":83517,"text":"where do you really want to go when you\nreally need to get something done?"},{"time":87055,"text":"You'll find out that people don't say\nwhat businesses think they would say."},{"time":90805,"text":"If you ask people the question:"},{"time":92326,"text":"Where do you need to go\nwhen you need to get something done?"},{"time":95166,"text":"Typically, you get three different\nkinds of answers."},{"time":97664,"text":"One is kind of a place\nor a location or a room."},{"time":100551,"text":"Another one is a moving object,"},{"time":102519,"text":"and a third is a time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104210,"text":"So here are some examples."},{"time":106246,"text":"I've been asking people this question\nfor about 10 years:"},{"time":109501,"text":"\"Where do you go when you\nreally need to get something done?\""},{"time":112681,"text":"I'll hear things like, the porch,\nthe deck, the kitchen."},{"time":116253,"text":"I'll hear things like\nan extra room in the house,"},{"time":119325,"text":"the basement,"},{"time":120626,"text":"the coffee shop, the library."},{"time":123547,"text":"And then you'll hear\nthings like the train,"},{"time":126126,"text":"a plane, a car -- so, the commute."},{"time":129666,"text":"And then you'll hear people say,"},{"time":131402,"text":"\"Well, it doesn't really\nmatter where I am,"},{"time":133428,"text":"as long as it's early in the morning\nor late at night or on the weekends.\""},{"time":136964,"text":"You almost never hear\nsomeone say, \"The office.\""},{"time":139813,"text":"But businesses are spending all this money\non this place called the office,"},{"time":143409,"text":"and they're making people\ngo to it all the time,"},{"time":145687,"text":"yet people don't do work in the office."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147746,"text":"What is that about?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":148933,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":150417,"text":"Why is that? Why is that happening?"},{"time":154093,"text":"And what you find out is,"},{"time":155387,"text":"if you dig a little bit deeper,\nyou find out that people --"},{"time":158799,"text":"this is what happens:"},{"time":160473,"text":"People go to work,"},{"time":162226,"text":"and they're basically\ntrading in their work day"},{"time":164560,"text":"for a series of \"work moments\" --\nthat's what happens at the office."},{"time":168076,"text":"You don't have a work day anymore.\nYou have work moments."},{"time":170783,"text":"It's like the front door\nof the office is like a Cuisinart,"},{"time":173585,"text":"and you walk in and your day\nis shredded to bits,"},{"time":175911,"text":"because you have 15 minutes here,\n30 minutes there,"},{"time":178483,"text":"and something else happens,\nyou're pulled off your work,"},{"time":181230,"text":"then you have 20 minutes, then it's lunch,\nthen you have something else to do ..."},{"time":185143,"text":"Then you've got 15 minutes, and someone\npulls you aside and asks you a question,"},{"time":188977,"text":"and before you know it, it's 5 p.m.,"},{"time":191197,"text":"and you look back on the day,"},{"time":192793,"text":"and you realize that you\ndidn't get anything done."},{"time":195848,"text":"We've all been through this."},{"time":197229,"text":"We probably went through it yesterday\nor the day before, or the day before that."},{"time":201056,"text":"You look back on your day,"},{"time":202494,"text":"and you're like,\n\"I got nothing done today."},{"time":204534,"text":"I was at work. I sat at my desk.\nI used my expensive computer."},{"time":209148,"text":"I used the software they told me to use."},{"time":211409,"text":"I went to these meetings\nI was asked to go to."},{"time":213886,"text":"I did these conference calls.\nI did all this stuff."},{"time":216607,"text":"But I didn't actually do anything."},{"time":219432,"text":"I just did tasks."},{"time":220608,"text":"I didn't actually get\nmeaningful work done.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":223447,"text":"And what you find is that,\nespecially with creative people --"},{"time":226407,"text":"designers, programmers,\nwriters, engineers, thinkers --"},{"time":232000,"text":"that people really need long stretches\nof uninterrupted time"},{"time":235912,"text":"to get something done."},{"time":237258,"text":"You cannot ask somebody\nto be creative in 15 minutes"},{"time":240710,"text":"and really think about a problem."},{"time":242353,"text":"You might have a quick idea,"},{"time":243743,"text":"but to be in deep thought about a problem\nand really consider a problem carefully,"},{"time":247726,"text":"you need long stretches\nof uninterrupted time."},{"time":250611,"text":"And even though the work day\nis typically eight hours,"},{"time":253337,"text":"how many people here have ever had\neight hours to themselves at the office?"},{"time":256916,"text":"How about seven hours?"},{"time":258107,"text":"Six? Five? Four?"},{"time":261339,"text":"When's the last time you had\nthree hours to yourself at the office?"},{"time":264515,"text":"Two hours? One, maybe?"},{"time":266561,"text":"Very, very few people actually have"},{"time":268300,"text":"long stretches of uninterrupted\ntime at an office."},{"time":270998,"text":"And this is why people\nchoose to do work at home,"},{"time":274552,"text":"or they might go to the office,"},{"time":276155,"text":"but they might go to the office\nreally early in the day,"},{"time":278814,"text":"or late at night when no one's around,"},{"time":280664,"text":"or they stick around\nafter everyone's left,"},{"time":282756,"text":"or go in on the weekends,"},{"time":284194,"text":"or they get work done on the plane,\nin the car or in the train,"},{"time":287309,"text":"because there are no distractions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289238,"text":"Now there are different\nkinds of distractions,"},{"time":291457,"text":"but not the really bad distractions,\nwhich I'll talk about in a minute."},{"time":294870,"text":"And this whole phenomenon of having\nshort bursts of time to get things done"},{"time":299358,"text":"reminds me of another thing\nthat doesn't work when you're interrupted,"},{"time":303024,"text":"and that is sleep."},{"time":304771,"text":"I think that sleep and work\nare very closely related --"},{"time":307984,"text":"not because you can work while you're\nsleeping and sleep while you're working."},{"time":311706,"text":"That's not really what I mean."},{"time":313174,"text":"I'm talking specifically about the fact\nthat sleep and work are phase-based,"},{"time":319269,"text":"or stage-based, events."},{"time":321324,"text":"Sleep is about sleep phases, or stages --\nsome people call them different things."},{"time":327403,"text":"There are five of them, and in order\nto get to the really deep ones,"},{"time":331261,"text":"the meaningful ones,\nyou have to go through the early ones."},{"time":334054,"text":"If you're interrupted while you're\ngoing through the early ones --"},{"time":337269,"text":"if someone bumps you in bed,\nor there's a sound, or whatever happens --"},{"time":341000,"text":"you don't just pick up where you left off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343024,"text":"If you're interrupted and woken up,"},{"time":345000,"text":"you have to start again."},{"time":346762,"text":"So you have to go back\na few phases and start again."},{"time":350000,"text":"And what ends up happening --\nyou might have days like this"},{"time":352791,"text":"where you wake up at eight or seven\nin the morning, or whenever you get up,"},{"time":356363,"text":"and you're like,\n\"I didn't sleep very well."},{"time":358503,"text":"I did the sleep thing --\nI went to bed, I laid down,"},{"time":361095,"text":"but I didn't really sleep.\""},{"time":363497,"text":"People say you go \"to\" sleep,"},{"time":365887,"text":"but you don't go to sleep,\nyou go towards sleep; it takes a while."},{"time":369029,"text":"You've got to go through phases and stuff,"},{"time":371108,"text":"and if you're interrupted,\nyou don't sleep well."},{"time":373441,"text":"So does anyone here\nexpect someone to sleep well"},{"time":375821,"text":"if they're interrupted all night?"},{"time":377427,"text":"I don't think anyone would say yes."},{"time":379165,"text":"Why do we expect people to work well"},{"time":381514,"text":"if they're being interrupted\nall day at the office?"},{"time":384010,"text":"How can we possibly expect\npeople to do their job"},{"time":386468,"text":"if they go to the office\nand are interrupted?"},{"time":388597,"text":"That doesn't really seem\nlike it makes a lot of sense, to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391528,"text":"So what are the interruptions that happen\nat the office but not at other places?"},{"time":395420,"text":"Because in other places, you can have\ninterruptions like the TV,"},{"time":399705,"text":"or you could go for a walk,\nor there's a fridge downstairs,"},{"time":403000,"text":"or you've got your own couch,\nor whatever you want to do."},{"time":406129,"text":"If you talk to certain managers,\nthey'll tell you"},{"time":408962,"text":"that they don't want\ntheir employees to work at home"},{"time":411557,"text":"because of these distractions."},{"time":413478,"text":"They'll sometimes also say,"},{"time":416533,"text":"\"If I can't see the person,\nhow do I know they're working?\""},{"time":419400,"text":"which is ridiculous, but that's one\nof the excuses that managers give."},{"time":422725,"text":"And I'm one of these managers.\nI understand. I know how this goes."},{"time":426006,"text":"We all have to improve\non this sort of thing."},{"time":428753,"text":"But oftentimes they'll cite distractions:"},{"time":430747,"text":"\"I can't let someone work at home."},{"time":432405,"text":"They'll watch TV, or do this other thing.\""},{"time":434445,"text":"It turns out those aren't\nthe things that are distracting,"},{"time":437204,"text":"Because those are voluntary distractions."},{"time":439184,"text":"You decide when you want\nto be distracted by the TV,"},{"time":441660,"text":"when you want to turn something on,"},{"time":443375,"text":"or when you want to go\ndownstairs or go for a walk."},{"time":445793,"text":"At the office,"},{"time":446968,"text":"most of the interruptions and distractions"},{"time":449015,"text":"that really cause people not\nto get work done are involuntary."},{"time":452156,"text":"So let's go through a couple of those."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455291,"text":"Now, managers and bosses\nwill often have you think"},{"time":458632,"text":"that the real distractions at work"},{"time":460660,"text":"are things like Facebook and Twitter"},{"time":463494,"text":"and YouTube and other websites,"},{"time":466688,"text":"and in fact, they'll go so far\nas to actually ban these sites at work."},{"time":470554,"text":"Some of you may work at places\nwhere you can't get to certain sites."},{"time":473919,"text":"I mean, is this China?\nWhat the hell is going on here?"},{"time":476562,"text":"You can't go to a website at work,\nand that's the problem?"},{"time":479329,"text":"That's why people aren't\ngetting work done,"},{"time":481361,"text":"because they're on Facebook and Twitter?"},{"time":483313,"text":"That's kind of ridiculous.\nIt's a total decoy."},{"time":486297,"text":"Today's Facebook and Twitter and YouTube,"},{"time":489738,"text":"these things are just\nmodern-day smoke breaks."},{"time":492000,"text":"No one cared about letting people take\na smoke break for 15 minutes 10 years ago,"},{"time":496039,"text":"so why does anyone care\nif someone goes to Facebook"},{"time":498681,"text":"or Twitter or YouTube here and there?"},{"time":500816,"text":"Those aren't the real\nproblems in the office."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503417,"text":"The real problems are\nwhat I like to call the M&amp;Ms,"},{"time":507052,"text":"the Managers and the Meetings."},{"time":509329,"text":"Those are the real problems\nin the modern office today."},{"time":512742,"text":"And this is why\nthings don't get done at work,"},{"time":515246,"text":"it's because of the M&amp;Ms."},{"time":517070,"text":"Now what's interesting is,"},{"time":519396,"text":"if you listen to all the places\nthat people talk about doing work,"},{"time":522561,"text":"like at home, in the car, on a plane,\nlate at night, or early in the morning,"},{"time":526549,"text":"you don't find managers and meetings."},{"time":528704,"text":"You find a lot of other distractions,\nbut not managers and meetings."},{"time":531965,"text":"So these are the things\nthat you don't find elsewhere,"},{"time":534966,"text":"but you do find at the office."},{"time":537371,"text":"And managers are basically people\nwhose job it is to interrupt people."},{"time":540746,"text":"That's pretty much what managers are for.\nThey're for interrupting people."},{"time":544262,"text":"They don't really do the work, so they\nmake sure everyone else is doing work,"},{"time":548125,"text":"which is an interruption."},{"time":549873,"text":"We have lots of managers in the world now,\nand a lot of people in the world,"},{"time":553491,"text":"and a lot of interruptions\nby these managers."},{"time":555616,"text":"They have to check in:\n\"Hey, how's it going?"},{"time":557693,"text":"Show me what's up.\" This sort of thing."},{"time":559601,"text":"They keep interrupting you\nat the wrong time,"},{"time":561783,"text":"while you're actually trying to do\nsomething they're paying you to do,"},{"time":565108,"text":"they tend to interrupt you."},{"time":566535,"text":"That's kind of bad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568122,"text":"But what's even worse is the thing\nthat managers do most of all,"},{"time":571257,"text":"which is call meetings."},{"time":572728,"text":"And meetings are just toxic,"},{"time":575298,"text":"terrible, poisonous things"},{"time":578324,"text":"during the day at work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579767,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":581007,"text":"We all know this to be true,"},{"time":582818,"text":"and you would never see a spontaneous\nmeeting called by employees."},{"time":586063,"text":"It doesn't work that way."},{"time":587348,"text":"The manager calls the meeting"},{"time":589100,"text":"so the employees can all come together,"},{"time":591039,"text":"and it's an incredibly disruptive\nthing to do to people --"},{"time":593786,"text":"to say, \"Hey look,"},{"time":595000,"text":"we're going to bring 10 people\ntogether right now and have a meeting."},{"time":598722,"text":"I don't care what you're doing,"},{"time":600238,"text":"you've got to stop doing it,\nso you can have this meeting.\""},{"time":603269,"text":"I mean, what are the chances\nthat all 10 people are ready to stop?"},{"time":606667,"text":"What if they're thinking about something\nimportant, or doing important work?"},{"time":610444,"text":"All of a sudden you tell them they have\nto stop doing that to do something else."},{"time":614257,"text":"So they go into a meeting room,\nthey get together,"},{"time":617000,"text":"and they talk about stuff\nthat doesn't really matter, usually."},{"time":620296,"text":"Because meetings aren't work."},{"time":621964,"text":"Meetings are places to go\nto talk about things"},{"time":624154,"text":"you're supposed to be doing later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625875,"text":"But meetings also procreate."},{"time":627870,"text":"So one meeting tends\nto lead to another meeting,"},{"time":630159,"text":"which leads to another meeting."},{"time":631668,"text":"There's often too many people\nin the meetings,"},{"time":633898,"text":"and they're very, very expensive\nto the organization."},{"time":636647,"text":"Companies often think of a one-hour\nmeeting as a one-hour meeting,"},{"time":639796,"text":"but that's not true,\nunless there's only one person."},{"time":642281,"text":"If there are 10 people, it's a 10-hour\nmeeting, not a one-hour meeting."},{"time":645829,"text":"It's 10 hours of productivity taken\nfrom the rest of the organization"},{"time":649130,"text":"to have this one-hour meeting,\nwhich probably should have been handled"},{"time":652493,"text":"by two or three people\ntalking for a few minutes."},{"time":655000,"text":"But instead, there's a long\nscheduled meeting,"},{"time":657563,"text":"because meetings are scheduled\nthe way software works,"},{"time":660158,"text":"which is in increments of 15 minutes,\nor 30 minutes, or an hour."},{"time":663583,"text":"You don't schedule an eight-hour meeting\nwith Outlook; you can't."},{"time":667250,"text":"You can go 15 minutes or 30 minutes\nor 45 minutes or an hour."},{"time":670248,"text":"And so we tend to fill these times up"},{"time":672246,"text":"when things should go really quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":674429,"text":"So meetings and managers are\ntwo major problems in businesses today,"},{"time":678103,"text":"especially at offices."},{"time":679286,"text":"These things don't exist\noutside of the office."},{"time":682428,"text":"So I have some suggestions\nto remedy the situation."},{"time":687253,"text":"What can managers do --"},{"time":689000,"text":"enlightened managers, hopefully --"},{"time":691000,"text":"what can they do to make the office\na better place for people to work,"},{"time":694496,"text":"so it's not the last resort,\nbut it's the first resort,"},{"time":697365,"text":"so that people start to say,"},{"time":698731,"text":"\"When I really want to get stuff done,\nI go to the office.\""},{"time":701532,"text":"Because the offices are well-equipped;"},{"time":703470,"text":"everything is there\nfor them to do the work."},{"time":705628,"text":"But they don't want to go there right\nnow, so how do we change that?"},{"time":708913,"text":"I have three suggestions\nto share with you."},{"time":710971,"text":"I have about three minutes,\nso that'll fit perfectly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":713866,"text":"We've all heard\nof the Casual Friday thing."},{"time":716727,"text":"I don't know if people still do that."},{"time":718600,"text":"But how about \"No-talk Thursdays?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":720300,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":722356,"text":"Pick one Thursday once a month,"},{"time":725326,"text":"and cut it in half, just the afternoon --\nI'll make it easy for you."},{"time":728661,"text":"So just the afternoon, one Thursday."},{"time":730415,"text":"First Thursday of the month,\njust the afternoon,"},{"time":732693,"text":"nobody in the office\ncan talk to each other."},{"time":734781,"text":"Just silence, that's it."},{"time":736343,"text":"And what you'll find"},{"time":738000,"text":"is that a tremendous amount\nof work gets done"},{"time":740432,"text":"when no one talks to each other."},{"time":742060,"text":"This is when people\nactually get stuff done,"},{"time":744148,"text":"is when no one's bothering them\nor interrupting them."},{"time":746688,"text":"Giving someone four hours\nof uninterrupted time"},{"time":749673,"text":"is the best gift you can\ngive anybody at work."},{"time":751871,"text":"It's better than a computer,"},{"time":753308,"text":"better than a new monitor,\nbetter than new software,"},{"time":756086,"text":"or whatever people typically use."},{"time":758085,"text":"Giving them four hours\nof quiet time at the office"},{"time":760513,"text":"is going to be incredibly valuable."},{"time":762458,"text":"If you try that, I think you'll agree,\nand hopefully you can do it more often."},{"time":766450,"text":"So maybe it's every other week,"},{"time":768196,"text":"or every week, once a week,"},{"time":770000,"text":"afternoons no one can talk to each other."},{"time":772077,"text":"That's something that you'll find\nwill really, really work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775188,"text":"Another thing you can try,"},{"time":777514,"text":"is switching from active\ncommunication and collaboration,"},{"time":781000,"text":"which is like face-to-face stuff --\ntapping people on the shoulder,"},{"time":784215,"text":"saying hi to them, having meetings,"},{"time":786215,"text":"and replace that with more\npassive models of communication,"},{"time":789025,"text":"using things like email\nand instant messaging,"},{"time":791350,"text":"or collaboration products,\nthings like that."},{"time":794628,"text":"Now some people might say\nemail is really distracting,"},{"time":797573,"text":"I.M. is really distracting, and these\nother things are really distracting,"},{"time":801167,"text":"but they're distracting at a time\nof your own choice and your own choosing."},{"time":804763,"text":"You can quit the email app;\nyou can't quit your boss."},{"time":807595,"text":"You can quit I.M.;"},{"time":809397,"text":"you can't hide your manager."},{"time":811238,"text":"You can put these things away,"},{"time":813000,"text":"and then you can be interrupted\non your own schedule, at your own time,"},{"time":816405,"text":"when you're available,\nwhen you're ready to go again."},{"time":818906,"text":"Because work, like sleep,\nhappens in phases."},{"time":821000,"text":"So you'll be going up, doing some work,"},{"time":823117,"text":"and then you'll come down from that work,"},{"time":825100,"text":"and then maybe it's time\nto check that email or I.M."},{"time":827576,"text":"There are very, very few things\nthat are that urgent,"},{"time":830101,"text":"that need to happen, that need\nto be answered right this second."},{"time":833172,"text":"So if you're a manager,"},{"time":834371,"text":"start encouraging people to use\nmore things like I.M. and email"},{"time":837379,"text":"and other things that someone can put away"},{"time":839419,"text":"and then get back to you\non their own schedule."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841644,"text":"And the last suggestion I have is that,"},{"time":845247,"text":"if you do have a meeting coming up,"},{"time":847000,"text":"if you have the power, just cancel it."},{"time":850650,"text":"Just cancel that next meeting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":852134,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":853324,"text":"Today's Friday, usually people\nhave meetings on Monday."},{"time":855993,"text":"Just don't have it."},{"time":857179,"text":"I don't mean move it;"},{"time":858608,"text":"I mean just erase it\nfrom memory, it's gone."},{"time":861274,"text":"And you'll find out that everything\nwill be just fine."},{"time":863886,"text":"All these discussions and decisions\nyou thought you had to make"},{"time":866926,"text":"at this one time at 9 a.m. on Monday,"},{"time":868734,"text":"just forget about them,\nand things will be fine."},{"time":871055,"text":"People will have a more open morning,\nthey can actually think."},{"time":874060,"text":"You'll find out all these things\nyou thought you had to do,"},{"time":876859,"text":"you don't actually have to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":878336,"text":"So those are just three quick suggestions\nI wanted to give you guys to think about."},{"time":882352,"text":"I hope that some of these ideas\nwere at least provocative enough"},{"time":885401,"text":"for managers and bosses\nand business owners"},{"time":887531,"text":"and organizers and people\nwho are in charge of other people,"},{"time":890371,"text":"to think about laying off a little bit,"},{"time":892266,"text":"and giving people more time\nto get work done."},{"time":894425,"text":"I think it'll all pay off in the end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":896259,"text":"So, thanks for listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":898285,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}